WEBVTT

00:00.034 --> 00:06.024
us for the weeks, then you probably know we are working through the topic of transformation.

00:06.705 --> 00:09.971
We've been doing this for a little while, and we're going to keep doing it for a while.

00:10.772 --> 00:19.267
And today, I'm just going to say the thing out loud, which is it's a bit of a weird Sunday.

00:19.908 --> 00:23.474
Scout Sunday, not something really do much.

00:23.970 --> 00:25.471
Transfiguration Sunday.

00:26.012 --> 00:27.994
Also, some of you are like, what's that?

00:28.675 --> 00:33.359
Never heard that word before, much less calling it like the Sunday that we're celebrating.

00:34.820 --> 00:36.822
Let me back up.

00:36.842 --> 00:52.978
So the church calendar, as a whole, for centuries and centuries across the globe celebrates various holidays or events on a given Sunday, or at various points in the year.

00:53.378 --> 01:06.572
We all know of Christmas, we all know of Easter, and then the church worldwide has chosen at various points to put other things on the map of the church calendar.

01:07.433 --> 01:12.518
This coming Wednesday, as I've already said, is Ash Wednesday and begins a season of Lent.

01:13.479 --> 01:19.666
I've brought Lent to the church when I first got here because I remember growing up as a kid,

01:19.746 --> 01:27.595
walking into an Easter Sunday where everyone's talking about how awesome Easter is and me thinking, oh, it's Easter.

01:27.795 --> 01:30.138
I guess we're doing that this Sunday.

01:30.659 --> 01:32.681
And it felt way too casual.

01:33.062 --> 01:37.987
It felt like, oh, I missed the opportunity for the lead-up.

01:39.049 --> 01:43.634
And for those of you who celebrate Christmas, as we all do,

01:43.714 --> 01:46.758
We know that it's the lead up to Christmas.

01:46.819 --> 01:49.422
It's the excitement of it and the anticipation.

01:49.482 --> 01:53.949
It's the build up to the big day that makes the big day special.

01:55.191 --> 01:58.315
Easter is similar but different.

01:59.717 --> 02:03.823
Ash Wednesday and Lent begins this process.

02:04.404 --> 02:11.154
It's really the process that I'm talking about and have been talking about and we'll be talking about for a while of transformation.

02:11.522 --> 02:25.659
It's this opportunity to dig down deep and to be intentional about the practices that we practice, the things that we say that we love, the things that we give up, the new things that we take on.

02:25.700 --> 02:34.651
And the hope is at the end of the 40 days of Lent, you get to Easter and a real resurrection happens.

02:35.171 --> 02:40.658
Of course, Jesus' resurrection that we will all celebrate together and it will be festive,

02:40.866 --> 02:42.689
That would be wonderful as a community.

02:42.749 --> 02:48.777
But the hope, too, is that there's a work that God will have been doing in your hearts.

02:49.318 --> 02:55.146
So at the end of Lent, something genuinely new is popping up into your life.

02:55.987 --> 02:59.653
I think that's what Lent in the season of Lent offers to all of us.

02:59.733 --> 03:06.322
Well, if you just back up a few days to, well, today, Transfiguration Sunday,

03:06.562 --> 03:12.160
Now normally I don't talk about transfiguration Sunday, like ever, except maybe one other time.

03:12.200 --> 03:14.909
But this time was different.

03:15.431 --> 03:16.334
And here's why.

03:16.354 --> 03:17.618
You see,

03:18.018 --> 03:28.872
The word metamorphosis is the word we all know from our days of being kids and caterpillars going into butterflies.

03:29.353 --> 03:30.755
We know what metamorphosis is.

03:31.235 --> 03:35.261
This is a good Greek word, and it really only shows up twice in our New Testament.

03:35.621 --> 03:37.504
We've already talked about these passages.

03:37.544 --> 03:42.450
One is Romans, chapter 12, where to be transformed by the renewing of our minds.

03:42.871 --> 03:45.234
The other is in 2 Corinthians 3.

03:45.634 --> 03:54.866
And this is another one that we've already talked about at length, which is about being transformed by what we behold, right, if you remember this sermon.

03:56.027 --> 04:02.695
But truth be told, the word actually does show up three other times, well, two other times, we'll say three.

04:04.077 --> 04:07.101
And it's this word right here, it's transfiguration.

04:07.401 --> 04:14.290
And why the translators chose to use transfiguration instead of just transformation, I don't know,

04:14.530 --> 04:15.912
It's the same exact word.

04:15.932 --> 04:31.092
We easily could have called this transformation Sunday in the passage that was read this morning from Matthew 17 about Jesus' transfiguration could very easily have been understood as Jesus' transformation.

04:31.132 --> 04:33.776
And it's the same thing.

04:33.796 --> 04:44.530
And so I thought to myself, well, of all years to celebrate transfiguration Sunday, this is the year because this is what we're talking about.

04:45.154 --> 04:48.118
And then that got me thinking about any number of other things.

04:48.739 --> 04:52.144
And of course, that is what I want to share with you in the sermon.

04:52.665 --> 04:54.868
But before we do, let's pray together.

04:57.632 --> 05:09.409
God, our Father in heaven, you sent your son Jesus Christ as a baby who grew into a man who lived.

05:10.851 --> 05:13.074
He taught us how to live.

05:14.786 --> 05:22.454
And he showed us the way, and he raised up disciples, and he showed them the way.

05:25.337 --> 05:28.280
And then, Lord, he died for us.

05:28.961 --> 05:37.931
He went to Calvary, and he again showed us the way that eternal life begins with his death.

05:37.991 --> 05:39.833
But it doesn't actually end there.

05:40.454 --> 05:44.658
It starts, but then he is raised from the dead.

05:46.370 --> 06:12.069
And with that simple act, that singular act in history, Lord, you have made a way for all of us to die to the things that we need to die to and to be raised anew, a new being, a new way of walking through the world, a life that has been energized by your life.

06:12.970 --> 06:15.474
And so God today, on this Sunday,

06:16.706 --> 06:23.815
We ask, Lord, that you begin to stir in our hearts those places where you so desperately and deeply want to change us.

06:24.135 --> 06:25.637
In Christ's holy name we pray.

06:26.298 --> 06:26.558
Amen.

06:28.360 --> 06:31.965
All right, so today we are indeed talking about the transfiguration.

06:31.985 --> 06:33.046
We already read the passage.

06:33.066 --> 06:34.788
I don't need to reread that for you.

06:34.808 --> 06:43.058
Hopefully you were paying attention as you've maybe heard the story before, but it's not the most common one, right?

06:43.234 --> 06:47.739
You may not know where this sits in the story of Jesus himself.

06:47.779 --> 06:49.060
So here's where it sits.

06:50.342 --> 06:54.006
Peter has just confessed to Jesus.

06:54.867 --> 06:57.970
Like Jesus asks this disciple, who are people saying that I am?

06:58.591 --> 07:03.637
And Peter gets the answer right and says, you are the Christ, son of the living God.

07:04.578 --> 07:06.199
And then Jesus says, you've got it.

07:07.741 --> 07:10.604
You can see what it seems other people can't see.

07:10.664 --> 07:12.146
And then he says,

07:12.226 --> 07:16.411
Now I must go to Jerusalem and die and be raised again."

07:17.533 --> 07:18.994
And Peter's, of course, confused by this.

07:19.074 --> 07:28.066
And then the very next scene is the transfiguration where Jesus takes three disciples, Peter and two others, and they go up on a mountain.

07:28.106 --> 07:38.098
And then before the three disciples, well, Jesus turns bright white and then Elijah and Moses appear.

07:39.490 --> 07:44.136
And then there's a booming voice from heaven that says, this is my beloved son.

07:44.196 --> 07:46.519
You should listen to him.

07:46.859 --> 07:47.780
That's what God says, right?

07:48.081 --> 07:49.082
You should listen to him.

07:50.324 --> 07:57.673
And then Peter kind of stammers around and he's like, I should set up some tents for you guys.

07:57.773 --> 08:08.146
Like I should do something and then Jesus kind of quiets him and then pretty soon everyone's gone.

08:08.322 --> 08:10.544
And it's just Jesus by himself once again.

08:10.564 --> 08:14.568
This is very mysterious mystical experience.

08:14.628 --> 08:24.158
And this morning, I want you to reflect not on Jesus as much, though that too, of course, but on Peter.

08:24.518 --> 08:27.401
Like, what if you were Peter?

08:28.862 --> 08:32.106
Peter's probably like maybe 18 or something at this point.

08:32.126 --> 08:36.530
He's a young man, not too much older than

08:36.610 --> 09:02.130
y'all sitting in the front rows here, and he has this wild experience where he has been with Jesus for years and he has seen a lot of things happen, but this one might take the cake and he goes up the mountain and he's watching his master, his lord, the one he has just confessed is the Christ, suddenly

09:02.242 --> 09:08.568
Moses and Elijah up here, and then they're talking to Jesus, and Jesus is turning bright white.

09:09.189 --> 09:15.394
You better believe this is the kind of experience that Peter's gonna remember the rest of his life, right?

09:15.414 --> 09:18.758
I mean, you would, wouldn't you?

09:19.198 --> 09:20.139
I certainly would.

09:20.980 --> 09:22.521
And maybe just backing up a second.

09:23.882 --> 09:27.526
Do you have an experience in your life?

09:27.666 --> 09:31.890
Maybe not quite this dramatic, but kind of dramatic.

09:32.770 --> 09:34.412
Maybe a spiritual experience.

09:35.493 --> 09:39.177
I was listening to a gentleman interviewed this week.

09:39.197 --> 09:40.899
His name is Dale Allison.

09:41.800 --> 09:44.803
And he is a scholar of New Testament studies.

09:44.903 --> 09:47.066
And I greatly admire his work.

09:47.186 --> 09:48.247
I have for a long time.

09:48.267 --> 09:49.468
But I had never heard this story.

09:49.488 --> 09:51.891
He was telling a story about when he was 16.

09:51.911 --> 09:57.937
And he said he's standing out in the yard at night.

09:58.118 --> 09:59.920
And it was a clear sky.

10:00.440 --> 10:02.162
There were stars everywhere.

10:02.562 --> 10:13.118
And he said, I don't know how to explain it other than it seemed like all of the stars descended from heaven and just wrapped around me.

10:13.619 --> 10:19.368
And I knew that I was in the presence of God and it was warm and it was loving.

10:19.408 --> 10:31.026
And he said, ever since then, I have set my sights and heart on following the ways of God and wanting to proceed down the path of what God wants to do for me.

10:31.490 --> 10:35.457
This one experience for him, obviously very dramatic.

10:35.597 --> 10:37.080
I've not had one quite like that.

10:38.122 --> 10:41.087
But it has propelled his entire life.

10:41.227 --> 10:45.875
He's now an older man who's done lots of great scholarship over his lifetime.

10:46.476 --> 10:52.327
And it started when he was 16, and he had this divine experience.

10:52.347 --> 10:54.290
Similarly, though, maybe opposite,

10:54.402 --> 11:05.756
I was at the hypothermia shelter this week and on Monday night, I was cutting hair and I was sitting with a gentleman and I was cutting his hair.

11:06.977 --> 11:16.709
By the way, I don't have hair to cut, but I have been cutting my boy's hair for years, 18 years to be precise.

11:17.169 --> 11:20.473
And so I'm okay with it for men.

11:20.533 --> 11:24.338
I would never, ladies, you do not want me cutting your hair.

11:25.186 --> 11:27.369
But I can't highlight hair.

11:27.449 --> 11:28.971
This is true.

11:29.751 --> 11:32.635
I used to highlight candles here.

11:32.655 --> 11:38.161
So I'm there with a man who at present is homeless.

11:38.642 --> 11:40.264
He has no home.

11:40.284 --> 11:43.167
And I am trying to strike up a conversation.

11:43.288 --> 11:52.018
And so I say to him, hey, why don't you tell me a story about something that has happened in your life?

11:52.482 --> 11:56.967
that is like a powerful spiritual experience for you.

11:58.048 --> 11:59.330
And he said, oh, I've got one.

12:00.231 --> 12:08.561
When I was a very young man 20 years ago, there was a dark force in the room with me and I could see it.

12:09.161 --> 12:11.144
And it was pinning me to the bed.

12:11.784 --> 12:13.747
I couldn't breathe and I couldn't get up.

12:14.387 --> 12:16.610
I cried out in Jesus name and it left.

12:18.252 --> 12:20.274
I thought, well, that is.

12:20.802 --> 12:22.864
powerful experience, indeed.

12:23.265 --> 12:26.128
Again, opposite, but no doubt.

12:26.428 --> 12:28.310
So he immediately like knew.

12:28.791 --> 12:29.351
He was ready.

12:29.692 --> 12:31.253
And so he tells me this.

12:31.374 --> 12:50.194
And then he says, again, this experience has propelled him through his life to be a spiritually minded man because he knows no other way to understand and explain the world around him other than through the lens of

12:50.306 --> 12:51.488
the spiritual realm.

12:55.054 --> 13:02.185
Peter, when he's a young man, he has this very spiritual experience with Jesus.

13:02.646 --> 13:04.488
No doubt he actually probably had many.

13:04.549 --> 13:09.236
He saw things we would all love to have seen or to see.

13:10.318 --> 13:12.882
But this one, this one's stuck with him.

13:12.922 --> 13:18.130
And we know this because when we're reading Peter's letters,

13:18.690 --> 13:21.113
He actually mentions this experience.

13:21.353 --> 13:32.547
If you will, like, turn with me to second Peter, chapter one, which is the text I want to read through for the sermon today.

13:32.607 --> 13:36.632
Second Peter is near the end of your New Testament.

13:36.692 --> 13:39.395
It's like just a couple books before Revelation.

13:40.096 --> 13:42.859
And we're in chapter one.

13:42.899 --> 13:48.306
As you're trying to find your way there, I'll read a little bit of the part that

13:48.834 --> 14:01.569
that connects what I want to say with the transfiguration because it's starting in about 16 where he clearly makes this connection in his mind.

14:02.350 --> 14:06.676
Peter, versus leading up to it, he says that he's an old man.

14:06.736 --> 14:08.318
He's dying at this point.

14:09.059 --> 14:15.186
And so the Peter who was 18 and had this transfiguration experience is now, I don't know,

14:15.266 --> 14:19.250
70, maybe 60, who knows how old he is at this point.

14:19.830 --> 14:23.734
He's nearing his death though, he says, and he remembers.

14:24.495 --> 14:37.047
And he says, we did not follow cleverly devised myths when we may known to you the power and coming of our Lord Jesus Christ, but we were eyewitnesses of his majesty.

14:37.427 --> 14:43.032
Like we saw, yeah, this isn't the passage yet, you can pull that down.

14:43.373 --> 14:44.914
He's saying we saw

14:46.210 --> 14:51.096
On that day, on that mountain, we were there when this thing happened.

14:51.997 --> 14:56.082
The honor and the glory that they were eyewitnesses to.

14:56.142 --> 15:04.151
So he says in verse 17, when we received honor and glory from God the Father and the voice was born to him by the majestic glory.

15:04.191 --> 15:07.595
And this is a key idea here is the glory.

15:07.635 --> 15:09.337
This is the white, the bright.

15:10.378 --> 15:13.682
This is my beloved son with whom I am well pleased, which is

15:15.426 --> 15:18.070
says on the mountain of transfiguration.

15:18.090 --> 15:27.345
He says, we ourselves heard this very voice born from heaven, for we were with him on that holy mountain.

15:27.365 --> 15:28.306
And again, here he is.

15:28.366 --> 15:30.069
Here's Peter at the end of his life.

15:30.129 --> 15:35.698
He's recalling that he had this experience and he saw Jesus transfigured.

15:36.226 --> 15:56.372
And then he says, we ourselves heard the voice and in verse 19, we have the prophetic word more fully confirmed to which you will do well to pay attention as to a lamp shining in a dark place until the day dawns and the morning star rises in your hearts.

15:57.153 --> 16:01.138
You will do well to pay attention, which is

16:01.282 --> 16:03.244
Basically what God said, right?

16:03.304 --> 16:06.307
So the booming voice says, this is my son whom I'm pleased with.

16:06.727 --> 16:09.570
And then God says, listen to him, right?

16:10.010 --> 16:11.232
Pay attention to him.

16:12.533 --> 16:19.319
And so now Peter, all these many years later is coming along and he's saying, look, we didn't just make this stuff up.

16:20.561 --> 16:22.542
We were eyewitnesses to it all.

16:24.604 --> 16:26.766
And we saw what happened to Jesus.

16:27.647 --> 16:30.450
We've relayed all of this to you.

16:30.754 --> 16:38.747
You can trust us and you would do well to pay attention, to listen to what he said.

16:38.787 --> 16:41.671
Okay.

16:41.691 --> 16:44.035
In some ways, that's the end of this sermon.

16:44.796 --> 16:58.418
If we would all do well, if we just paid a little more attention and listened more to what Jesus has said and is trying to do in us.

17:00.322 --> 17:05.026
The text I want to read from, however, is backed up in verse three.

17:05.066 --> 17:13.735
And this is where my tech team can put this back up and we'll read together how Peter starts this letter.

17:15.396 --> 17:29.970
He begins and he says, his divine power has granted to us all things that pertain to life and to godliness through the knowledge of him who called us

17:30.242 --> 17:33.246
to his own glory and excellence.

17:37.150 --> 17:38.392
There's a few things happening here.

17:40.394 --> 17:45.240
Peter, as I've said, is no longer the 18-year-old man boy.

17:45.280 --> 17:59.538
He's now a 70-year-old man who is weathered and has grown and has himself been transfigured or transformed.

17:59.842 --> 18:00.743
over a lifetime.

18:02.446 --> 18:09.316
And he's looking back on his life, and he's advising you and me and anyone who will listen to him in these letters.

18:10.398 --> 18:15.967
And he's telling us about how this transformation looks, how it works.

18:18.691 --> 18:20.774
And he's saying that he is a different man.

18:21.695 --> 18:22.717
And how does it happen?

18:22.777 --> 18:28.626
Well, it begins very... Sunday school answer.

18:29.346 --> 18:29.787
Jesus.

18:31.028 --> 18:32.350
It begins with Jesus.

18:33.331 --> 18:41.742
His divine power, which has been then granted, has been given, starts with Jesus.

18:42.162 --> 18:47.229
His divine power is granted to all of us, and it pertains to two things.

18:47.289 --> 18:54.738
And these are very important to me, and they should be to you to life, like an abundant kind of life life.

18:55.010 --> 19:06.009
a life that only Jesus can offer, a life that only God, the God of the universe who breathes life into everything, only that kind of life that can be offered by God.

19:06.029 --> 19:07.612
That is what we're talking about here.

19:08.193 --> 19:14.604
And then the second is godliness, which is you can't have godliness apart from God.

19:15.926 --> 19:20.754
And so if Jesus is the manifestation of God, then Jesus offers us

19:21.058 --> 19:21.999
these two things.

19:22.079 --> 19:27.826
He offers us this divine kind of life, and he offers us a path toward godliness.

19:28.307 --> 19:32.512
And if the path toward godliness sounds boring or dusty to you, I promise it's not.

19:32.933 --> 19:33.974
It's not intended to be.

19:34.014 --> 19:39.220
And it is filled with joy and all of the best things that life has to offer.

19:40.682 --> 19:43.826
And so this is what he wants, life and godliness.

19:44.130 --> 19:47.194
And then he says, through the knowledge of him.

19:47.254 --> 19:50.919
And here is where we might go off the rails if we're not careful.

19:51.279 --> 19:56.826
Because knowledge, as you and I often think of it, is a Greek word would be gnosis.

19:57.888 --> 20:03.675
It's like, if I can just shove the right things in my head, well, then I am a Christian, I guess.

20:04.736 --> 20:09.202
I would submit to you that there are many, many, many Christians

20:09.314 --> 20:16.083
who know all of the right things, but they do not have the kind of knowledge that is talked about right here in 2 Peter.

20:17.705 --> 20:21.110
This is not gnosis, this is epi-gnosis.

20:22.772 --> 20:24.795
Oh, so close, but also different.

20:25.276 --> 20:35.890
It is a deep kind of knowledge, a knowledge that comes not from like studying the right books, but a knowledge that comes from following a master.

20:37.058 --> 20:49.335
from doing what that person says to do, reaching him or her again and again and again and following in their steps and doing the kinds of things that they do.

20:50.116 --> 20:56.745
And so maybe it's like a chef and you are learning, you're the sous chef alongside the chef.

20:57.125 --> 20:59.789
And when they do some cutting, you do some cutting.

21:00.049 --> 21:04.335
And when they do some broiling, you do some broiling and you get the idea, right?

21:05.797 --> 21:06.738
Jesus here,

21:07.426 --> 21:10.611
Jesus is our chef and we are his sous chef.

21:11.953 --> 21:15.358
He is our master and we are his student.

21:16.419 --> 21:27.796
And we should be following in the footsteps of his ways and reading the things he reads, doing the things he does, watching how he lives his life.

21:28.598 --> 21:37.010
And so when he becomes transfigured, what he is offering us is not to say this is me and you're something different.

21:37.282 --> 21:39.525
He's actually showing us a way.

21:39.565 --> 21:44.212
And he's saying, I am showing you what transformation looks like.

21:44.712 --> 21:46.595
I'm showing you the end product, really.

21:46.635 --> 21:48.618
The goal of where you're trying to get to.

21:48.658 --> 21:55.187
And then he sets about the path of discipleship.

21:55.207 --> 21:56.308
And he says, just follow me.

21:57.750 --> 21:58.611
Watch what I'm doing.

21:59.633 --> 22:01.155
Make the motions that I'm making.

22:01.856 --> 22:03.538
Make the steps that I'm making.

22:03.714 --> 22:09.102
And if you can do this, you will find the ways of life and godliness.

22:11.465 --> 22:14.048
And then Peter keeps talking.

22:15.010 --> 22:32.274
And he says, through the knowledge of him who called us by his glory and by his excellence, and here I have to think he has in mind that fateful day on the Mount of Transfiguration, by which he has granted to us

22:32.354 --> 22:35.238
His precious and very great promises.

22:36.279 --> 22:42.588
Jesus is coming and He's offering us this way, this promise of life and life eternal.

22:43.730 --> 22:52.722
So that through them, and here is the most scandalous line I've come across in the Bible in a very long time, if you allow it to be.

22:54.562 --> 23:10.003
by which he has granted to us his precious and very great promises, so that through them, you may become partakers of the divine nature, so that you and I might become participant.

23:10.463 --> 23:14.769
The word here, partaker, participant, this is actually the word Koinaniya.

23:15.150 --> 23:17.373
We've had Koinaniya groups here, right?

23:17.393 --> 23:18.514
You remember Koinaniya?

23:19.295 --> 23:24.242
This is the coming together and having all things in common, right?

23:24.930 --> 23:27.794
But this is a different kind of commonality.

23:27.834 --> 23:33.623
It's a participation in God's very nature itself.

23:36.387 --> 23:45.942
And what I think Peter is offering to us, saying to us, is I saw Jesus glorified on the Mount of Transfiguration that day.

23:46.683 --> 23:49.207
I saw what it's supposed to all look like.

23:49.747 --> 23:54.194
I have an image of where I want to go and where we're all trying to get to.

23:55.138 --> 24:07.455
And God is calling us into that to participate in that kind of life, in the divine life itself, in God's very nature.

24:07.495 --> 24:11.360
And we all know what God's nature is, right?

24:12.522 --> 24:17.628
We've read Paul's fruit of the spirit, love and joy and peace and patience, et cetera.

24:19.090 --> 24:24.658
Peter is going to give us a few of his own, his own version of what that looks like and what follows.

24:25.474 --> 24:32.965
And so he goes on, he says, having escaped from the corruption that's in the world because of our sinful desire.

24:33.025 --> 24:53.714
And here, again, he has to have in mind that we've got these dual natures battling it out within us, this worldly base nature, the sinful desire that is warring against the divine nature that God is calling us into.

24:54.754 --> 24:59.741
and that Jesus himself has made a way to make it even possible to get there.

25:02.985 --> 25:04.507
And all of this requires what?

25:06.970 --> 25:12.397
Transformation, metamorphosis, the changing from a caterpillar into a butterfly.

25:12.437 --> 25:14.320
This is what he's talking about.

25:15.802 --> 25:22.290
So he goes on, for this very reason, make every effort to supplement your

25:22.850 --> 25:24.011
Note where he begins.

25:24.051 --> 25:28.056
He starts with the faith piece because this is where it all begins.

25:28.316 --> 25:29.277
It starts with faith.

25:29.978 --> 25:32.020
It starts by saying, yes, Jesus, I trust you.

25:32.360 --> 25:33.281
You've got the goods.

25:33.542 --> 25:34.763
You've got the way.

25:34.883 --> 25:36.745
I saw you on the Mount of Transfiguration.

25:37.026 --> 25:37.826
I saw the end.

25:37.846 --> 25:39.008
I believe that.

25:39.448 --> 25:42.031
And now I'm ready to start the journey.

25:43.413 --> 25:44.734
I'm ready to start following.

25:45.475 --> 25:49.379
I'm ready to call you my chef and I'll be your sous chef, right?

25:50.520 --> 25:52.082
And he goes on and he says,

25:53.218 --> 26:01.791
Make every effort to supplement your faith with virtue and then your virtue with knowledge.

26:01.931 --> 26:03.994
And this one actually is gnosis this time.

26:04.074 --> 26:21.380
It's like putting the right things in your head and knowledge with self control and self control with steadfastness and steadfastness with godliness and godliness with brotherly love or brotherly affection, Philadelphia.

26:22.021 --> 26:22.962
And finally,

26:23.522 --> 26:26.966
Adding to that is agape, love.

26:27.887 --> 26:52.978
For if these qualities are yours and are increasing, I love this idea, if these qualities are yours and they are increasing, well, they keep you from being ineffective or unfruitful in the knowledge of our Lord Jesus Christ, which is to say in the apprenticeship, in the deep knowledge,

26:53.538 --> 27:06.079
In the way of being Jesus as he is our master and we are his follower, for whoever lacks these qualities is nearsighted.

27:07.160 --> 27:08.743
He's blind, in fact.

27:09.444 --> 27:10.526
And what has he lost?

27:10.666 --> 27:11.608
What has he forgotten?

27:11.648 --> 27:17.938
Well, he has forgotten that he was cleansed from his former sins.

27:19.394 --> 27:21.396
There is so much in this passage.

27:21.736 --> 27:22.918
I'm gonna be honest with you.

27:23.518 --> 27:28.904
This is one of these passages where I jumped into it and I thought I was gonna say one thing and then it kept going.

27:29.264 --> 27:36.111
And there's like layer upon layer of what is happening here and is worthy of your reflection.

27:36.171 --> 27:42.698
And my guess is I could keep talking for like another two hours and it's just gonna flood the system.

27:43.298 --> 27:46.962
And so my request of you is that you take this passage home with you.

27:47.522 --> 28:16.082
and you read through it in earnest, what is the 70-year-old Peter trying to say to you after a lifetime of someone who's been transformed by the power of the Holy Spirit by being in contact with Jesus, his Lord, and being trained by Jesus over a lifetime, he's saying, well, it should look like an increasing kind of spiritual life.

28:17.794 --> 28:20.237
an increasing kind of virtue.

28:21.659 --> 28:27.046
Your character should be different at age 70 than it was at age 18.

28:29.390 --> 28:33.715
Peter himself, I think it's funny, he uses the examples he does.

28:35.297 --> 28:37.821
And the reason is because he's lived them.

28:37.861 --> 28:40.985
He uses the example of self-control.

28:41.506 --> 28:47.634
And if you know Peter, when you meet him in the gospels, he's like the opposite of self-control.

28:47.938 --> 28:52.143
He's the guy who jumps out of the boat way too quickly.

28:52.163 --> 28:58.089
He's the guy who when some soldier comes after Jesus, he slices his ear off.

28:58.109 --> 28:59.851
He's a guy without self-control.

29:01.413 --> 29:09.842
But over a lifetime of being mentored by Jesus, discipled by Jesus, transformed by Jesus.

29:10.944 --> 29:14.568
He's a man standing there saying, your self-control matters deeply.

29:15.248 --> 29:16.690
We even see it actually.

29:16.866 --> 29:23.372
in Acts 4 where he has a tremendous amount of self-control in front of the Sanhedrin.

29:23.993 --> 29:26.415
Or he says, steadfastness, right?

29:26.836 --> 29:28.998
This is another one of his virtues here.

29:29.038 --> 29:38.307
You should be a steadfast kind of person, says the guy who three times before the rooster crows denies Jesus.

29:39.368 --> 29:41.730
He's the opposite of steadfast, right?

29:41.750 --> 29:46.034
When the going off, Peter got going.

29:46.658 --> 29:47.279
He left.

29:49.322 --> 29:55.530
But after years, decades, nation, he's coming to you and to me.

29:56.131 --> 29:58.594
He's saying, we need to be steadfast kind of people.

29:58.935 --> 30:00.136
I wasn't always this way.

30:00.797 --> 30:04.843
But for a lifetime, I have been trained in the ways of Jesus.

30:06.925 --> 30:07.827
Brotherly love.

30:09.729 --> 30:16.338
His understanding of like what a brother was was very small, very small.

30:17.026 --> 30:21.152
He thought a brother was like his other Jewish comrades.

30:22.194 --> 30:29.044
And he had to learn that when that sheet comes down in Acts 10, and God says, no, no, no, all things are sacred.

30:30.046 --> 30:33.211
There is no such thing as that which is impure and pure.

30:33.251 --> 30:36.376
And he opens up the table to the Gentiles.

30:37.137 --> 30:41.263
He has to expand what it means to live with brotherly love.

30:42.305 --> 30:45.650
And so again, over the course of a lifetime,

30:45.826 --> 30:49.010
He is transformed by the person of Jesus.

30:51.032 --> 31:03.086
Therefore, brothers, verse 10, be all the more diligent to confirm your calling and election for if you practice these qualities, you will never fail.

31:03.787 --> 31:12.978
For in this way, there will be richly provided for you an entrance into the eternal kingdom of our Lord and Savior, Jesus Christ.

31:15.458 --> 31:27.875
I heard a stat this week that should cause every one of us to sit up and to grow very concerned about the state of the church in the United States and the world.

31:28.956 --> 31:44.978
The stat goes like this, a Barna study shows that only 8% of millennials who were raised Christian, we're not talking 8% of everybody, we're talking about 8% of millennials who were raised Christian

31:45.090 --> 32:03.890
in the church qualify as what Barnacle's resilient disciples, resilient disciples, which they then quantify as they attend church just once a month and engage with their faith community in that way.

32:04.951 --> 32:07.053
They trust firmly in the authority of Scripture.

32:07.994 --> 32:11.378
They're committed to Jesus personally, and a firm is death and resurrection.

32:11.618 --> 32:15.604
and they express a desire to let their faith shape their interaction with the culture.

32:15.624 --> 32:17.046
8% folks.

32:19.269 --> 32:22.734
That is an astonishing number.

32:22.754 --> 32:25.138
Again, this is not 8% of the whole culture.

32:26.500 --> 32:27.702
It would be much lower than that.

32:28.623 --> 32:36.034
This is 8% of those who grew up in church.

32:36.054 --> 32:41.522
The church does not have a gnosis problem, an information problem, a knowledge problem.

32:42.434 --> 32:45.177
It has a formation problem.

32:45.877 --> 32:47.619
It has an epignosis problem.

32:49.201 --> 32:59.711
We have all of the resources we could ever want with all of the information we could ever want, streaming on those devices that sit in our pockets.

33:00.271 --> 33:05.837
And if you wanted knowledge, it's sitting there all day long, ready to be pumped into your brain.

33:07.638 --> 33:09.460
That is not our trouble.

33:09.981 --> 33:11.442
Information is not our trouble.

33:12.226 --> 33:14.789
formation, formation.

33:15.029 --> 33:17.592
Who are we being formed into?

33:17.652 --> 33:21.997
Ultimately, transformation is our problem.

33:23.739 --> 33:24.880
And this is not just the kids.

33:25.461 --> 33:26.542
It's not just the millennials.

33:26.922 --> 33:28.044
It's not the Gen Xers.

33:28.444 --> 33:29.445
It's not the boomers.

33:29.505 --> 33:30.667
It's all of us.

33:32.088 --> 33:34.691
What are we being formed into?

33:34.731 --> 33:36.233
Is it?

33:38.716 --> 33:40.978
Peter says things like

33:41.154 --> 33:43.517
steadfastness and self-control?

33:44.839 --> 33:45.781
Or is it something else?

33:53.252 --> 33:58.319
When I think about what South Run should be, there's lots of things.

33:58.339 --> 34:01.424
The church should be lots of things, by the way, but it is a hospital.

34:01.444 --> 34:11.058
One of the ways in which the church has been cast is a hospital for the sick and the ability to bring people in and to revive them to health.

34:12.258 --> 34:25.335
But if I could add a layer to that, I'd love for it to be a school of transformation, like a place where you could go and you would know that, okay, well, there's a path here for me.

34:25.375 --> 34:34.606
I know now because I have this community and these resources, I know how to grow in the ways of Jesus.

34:34.626 --> 34:40.754
I have mentors ready to breathe life into me and show me the way.

34:41.058 --> 34:44.423
I have a small group who's ready to hold me accountable.

34:44.443 --> 35:02.126
I have people around me who are ready to show me the better way so that we don't end up with an 8% of folks walking through our church who are, what do they call them, resilient disciples, but that number is far higher.

35:04.069 --> 35:08.515
I would love for us to be known as a school for transformation.

35:09.817 --> 35:10.738
I'll be honest though.

35:11.394 --> 35:15.761
I don't know that anyone, and I really mean anyone has to give this out.

35:15.781 --> 35:19.387
And by anyone, I mean like churches in this day and age.

35:20.048 --> 35:25.577
I hear a lot of pastors talking about this exact problem for the reasons the stats kind of bring out.

35:26.579 --> 35:29.283
There isn't like a model that's sitting out there.

35:29.304 --> 35:35.313
And so maybe what I'm asking from you is how can you and I partner together?

35:35.333 --> 35:38.098
How can we all come together and say, this is really important.

35:38.562 --> 35:58.224
We want to be the kind of church that doesn't just like gather on Sundays so we can check that box, but like we want to be a church that actually changes people, like changes real lives, helps people to grow into who they should be and what God wants for them into the image of God that they were designed to always be.

35:59.425 --> 36:00.506
Exactly how we do that.

36:00.846 --> 36:07.794
What that looks like probably depends on the person, but I'd love for us to be a church that is like that.

36:08.226 --> 36:09.948
I think this is what God is calling us into.

36:11.009 --> 36:17.155
And as I'm thinking about a year of transformation, this is like right here at the front of my mind.

36:18.216 --> 36:18.857
Let's pray together.

36:22.401 --> 36:35.154
Father in heaven, I'm gripped by the fact that our culture is slowly walking away.

36:36.450 --> 36:51.369
And even our church culture, Lord, is drifting from ways of being Christ followers that I think we all assumed were just there.

36:53.572 --> 36:57.557
But over the years, we have found our ways down other roads.

36:58.959 --> 37:00.461
But God, it need not be this way.

37:01.642 --> 37:04.626
You have given the church

37:05.026 --> 37:20.987
as your bride for 2,000 years now to be that hospital or that school for transformation or that place where you dwell, the body of Christ itself, working the ways of Christ in the world.

37:22.789 --> 37:25.192
God, I pray that South Run be that kind of place.

37:26.454 --> 37:33.042
And Lord, for each person in here, the message that they take away is their message.

37:34.466 --> 37:40.953
Because at the very least, at the very least, you are calling them into a life of transformation.

37:40.993 --> 37:42.535
This isn't a season.

37:42.575 --> 37:43.977
This isn't a moment.

37:44.397 --> 37:48.822
This is a life ever increasing, ever increasing.

37:51.506 --> 37:55.250
So one day we meet you in glory.

37:55.270 --> 37:57.813
We see you face to face.

37:57.833 --> 38:02.418
We're drawn into your presence and the fullness we all desire.

38:04.482 --> 38:15.114
God, as we go out this week, about our business, it's so easy to get trapped up in the ways of the world.

38:16.816 --> 38:27.828
Things that pull us down into the depths, that teach us to rise above, to see the world as you see it, and to live transformed lives.

38:28.869 --> 38:29.650
Christ's Holy Name.

